<!-- INSTRUCTION MODAL -->
<div class="modal fade" id="instructionModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="instructionModalLabel" aria-hidden="false">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl">
        <div class="modal-header bg-black">
            <h4 class="modal-title font-weight-bold text-white mx-auto">CHARACTER CREATION</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-body">

                <h6 class="text-center font-weight-bold"><strong>STEP I:</strong> ADJUST ATTRIBUTES, SEX, OR STRATEGY (GREEN BORDERS)</h6>
                <ul>
                    <li>Attribute Points are determined by the Character's initial WILLPOWER Roll divided by TWO</li>
                    <li>An Attribute can only be increased, there is no reducing it below the original value to gain extra Attribute Points</li>
                    <li>Attribute Maximum is 20</li>
                    <li>If a Character's WILLPOWER is greater than 12 you may change their STRATEGY which will generate a new BACKGROUND</li>
                    <li>BACKGROUND determines initial skillset and additional Skill Choices</li>
                    <li>WILLPOWER determines the base number of Skill Choices, regardless of BACKGROUND</li>
                    <li>All initial SKILLS are directly determined by the Character's ATTRIBUTES.  Choose Wisely</li>
                </ul>
                <h6 class="text-center font-weight-bold"><strong>STEP II:</strong> SELECT THE CHARACTERS SKILLS</h6>
                <ul>
                    <li>Spend Skill Points to IMPROVE existing skills (Colored Borders) or ADD NEW skills (Blue Buttons)</li>
                    <li>Yellow Buttons and Yellow Borders cost ONE Skill Point to Select or Improve (+2D10) respectively (Max = 150)</li>
                    <li>Red Buttons and Red Borders cost TWO Skill Points to Select or Improve (+D10) respectively (Max = 150, Dodge Max = 50, Off Hand Max = 0 )</li>
                    <li>Gray Buttons represent a Skill Focus and increase the Likelihood of Success for ALL other Skills related to the Focus (Max = 50)</li>
                </ul>
                <h6 class="text-center font-weight-bold"><strong>STEP III:</strong> CLICK SUBMIT AT BOTTOM OF PAGE</h6>
                <hr />
                <h6 class="text-center font-weight-bold">TIPS &amp; TRICKS</h6>
                <ul>
                    <li>The Taskbar (Top of Page) will display the Character's remaining Trait Points, Skill Points, and Free Skill Choices resulting from BACKGROUND</li>
                    <li>If you are unhappy with your Character's original rolls feel free to REFRESH the page at any time</li>
                    <li>Substantial NEGATIVE MODIFIERS apply to both SKILLS and ATTRIBUTES in a wide variety of scenarios, hence the 100+ Skill Rating Cap</li>
                    <li>A "Jack-of-all-Trades" is infinitely more likely to survive than the "Master-of-One"</li>
                    <li>This is just the beginning of your Character's story.  All aspects of your Character can be improved with sufficient EXPERIENCE gain</li>
                    <li>Think of low valued Attributes as the effect of the "Traumas of the Apocalypse" rather than a genetic deficiency.  Coping mechanisms, anti-social behavior, malnutrition, atrophy, old injuries, anxiety, etc.
                    are all very real aspects of the Human Experience</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-success border border-dark mx-auto" data-dismiss="modal">READY</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

